began with Vol. 1 No. 1 (May 17, 1902) ; print ceased with in May 18, 1929. Editor: C.C. Goodwin 1902-1918; J.T. Goodwin, 1918- Includes special Christmas issues in illustrated magazine format, 1911-1918. Numbering dropped with August 18, 1917. Vol. 1, No. 1 (May 17, 1902); title from cover (Chronicling America website, viewed Dec. 9, 2020). June 21, 1919 (Chronicling America website, viewed Dec. 9, 2020)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:30.200Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2020221650/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["salt lake", "utah", "salt lake city", "united states"], "number": ["online resource", "2020221650", "904431579", "2766-4392", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "goodwin's weekly : a thinking paper for thinking people (salt lake city, utah) 1902-1929 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 47.46009, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD F821", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["illustrated works", "pictorial works", "newspapers", "salt lake city (utah)", "united states", "salt lake", "utah", "salt lake city"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:59:43.327Z", "title": "Goodwin's weekly : a thinking paper for thinking people", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2020221650/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2020221662/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1890", "dates": ["[1890 TO 9999]"], "description": ["Weekly (Sunday only) Print began with v. 38, no. 115 (Feb. 25, 1890). Publisher varies. Continues the numbering of: Salt Lake daily tribune. Semiweekly ed.: Salt Lake semi-weekly tribune, 1894-1902. Weekly ed.: Salt Lake weekly tribune (Salt Lake City, Utah : 1902), 1902-<>. Other eds.: Salt Lake tribune (Salt Lake City, U